    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A megilp or gel medium for oil painting, introduced in the United States in the 1940s by Jacques Maroger, a painter and conservator.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
